## **Description**
The **System Variable **operator allows to return a system variable based on the configuration settings.

## **Input**
None.

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**out0**

String

The system variable defined in the configuration settings

## **Settings**
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

- From the **Variable **drop-down menu, select the system variable that the operator will return. The available options are:

**Variable**

**Description**

**$InputFileName**

Name of the input file

**$workUnit**

Name of the work unit

**$InputFilePath**

Path of the input file

**$InputFileFullNa me**

Full path and name of the input file

**$InputFileId**

Numeric ID of the input file

**$InputFileSize**

Size (in bytes) of the input file

**$InstanceID**

Instance number of the DTE software service

**$InstanceStartDa te**

Start date of the DTE software service process

**$Custom_xx**

Customizable variables provided at execution time in the production environment

- From the **Reader **drop-down menu, select the Reader component to use for the file used to extract the desired system information.

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

## **Special cases**
None.
